gaffer.operation

Interface GetOperation<SEED_TYPE,RETURN_TYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    SEED_TYPE - the seed type of the operation. This must be JSON serialisable.
    RETURN_TYPE - the result type of the operation. This must be JSON serialisable.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Operation<Iterable<SEED_TYPE>,Iterable<RETURN_TYPE>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAccumuloTwoSetSeededOperation, AbstractGetOperation, GetAdjacentEntitySeeds, GetAllEdges, GetAllElements, GetAllEntities, GetEdges, GetEdgesBetweenSets, GetEdgesBySeed, GetEdgesInRanges, GetEdgesWithinSet, GetElements, GetElementsBetweenSets, GetElementsInRanges, GetElementsSeed, GetElementsWithinSet, GetEntities, GetEntitiesBySeed, GetEntitiesInRanges, GetRelatedEdges, GetRelatedElements, GetRelatedEntities, UpdateCache

    public interface GetOperation<SEED_TYPE,RETURN_TYPE>
extends Operation<Iterable<SEED_TYPE>,Iterable<RETURN_TYPE>>
    A GetOperation defines a seeded get operation to be processed on a graph.

    Get operations have several flags to determine how to filter Elements.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  GetOperation.IncludeEdgeType
      A IncludeEdgeType defines whether Edges used in the operation should be directed.
      static class  GetOperation.IncludeIncomingOutgoingType
      A IncludeIncomingOutgoingType defines the direction of the Edges during the operation.
      static class  GetOperation.SeedMatchingType
      A SeedMatchingType defines how the seeds in the operation should be matched.
